GranWarrioricPirate: There are laws here in Canada protecting individual's privacy against governments and corporations, but they often get ignored so we need an escape, something where we control our own data. Also, a data/privacy ombudsman would be nice, that would certainly help. Maybe there is one, maybe folks just aren't aware. If so, that would be handy information. 

When it comes to information we adults need: most of the time we're trying to figure out how to pursue a hobby or career. When I was younger I was fortunate both my parents are doctors so their actual jobs were readily available for me to learn about, but as an adult I still think I know less about doctors and law etc... then most kids do because I never picked up a kid's book to learn about it.
